author: CNN
description: Hamas said it has handed over all hostage remains it can access, saying “significant efforts and special equipment” are needed to recover the remaining dead captives in Gaza. A source told CNN that Israel believes Hamas has access to at least six other bodies. After initially limiting aid deliveries in retaliation, Israeli and US officials say Israel is now allowing the amount of aid into Gaza required under the ceasefire agreement, including fuel and gas. CNN's Christiane Amanpour speaks with Nasser Al-Kidwa, Former Palestinian Authority Foreign Minister and nephew of the late Yasser Arafat, about the ceasefire between Israel and Hamas.   #CNN #News #amanpour
title: Tensions Rise Just Days Into Gaza Ceasefire between Israel and Hamas

author: CNN
description: Federal prosecutors seized $15 billion in cryptocurrency from an investment scheme known as “pig butchering” that they allege emanated from forced labor camps in Cambodia. CNN's Kara Scannell reports.
title: Feds seize record $15B in Bitcoin from 'pig butchering' scheme

author: CNN
description:
La Niña is back, the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration says. Its cooler Pacific waters combined with a “blob” of warm water could rewrite the US winter script and herald the return of the polar vortex later in the season.
#cnn #news
title: La Niña Returns, Hinting at a Wetter and Wilder Winter Ahead

author: CNN
description: Graham Platner, a Marine veteran turned oyster farmer who is now a rising Democratic Senate candidate in Maine, once called himself a “communist,” dismissed “all” police as bastards, and said rural White Americans “actually are” racist and stupid, according to deleted social media posts reviewed by CNN’s KFile. #CNN #News
title: Deleted posts show Maine Senate Candidate's raw views on politics

author: CNN
description: John Bolton, President Donald Trump’s former national security adviser-turned-adversary, has been indicted by a federal grand jury in Maryland, according to two sources. title: John Bolton indicted by federal grand jury

author: CNN
description: Video shows a Border Patrol agent restraining a man who says he's a US citizen outside a Chicago Walgreens store. The incident happened after a Border Patrol vehicle collided with an SUV during an immigration enforcement operation on Tuesday. CNN has reached out to DHS for comment on the incident.
title: ICE detains 19 year old outside Walgreens

description: US President Donald Trump said on social media Thursday that he would meet with Russian President Vladimir Putin in Budapest, though he did not specify when that meeting may take place.  #CNN #News
title: Trump says he will meet with Putin in Budapest to discuss war in Ukraine

author: CNN
description: John Hartman is a fifth generation soybean farmer in Morengo, Illinois who tells CNN’s Whitney Wild his crops’ decrease in value is in part due to a “man-made crisis” caused by President Donald Trump and his escalating trade war with China.
title: Farmer on crops' decrease in value: 'Man-made crisis caused by Donald Trump'

author: CNN
description: Spanish ultrarunner Kilian Jornet speaks with CNN’s Kate Bolduan after completing an audacious link up of all of the 14,000-foot mountains in Colorado, California and Washington. Jornet’s ”States of Elevation” journey covered 3,198 miles, 403,638 feet of climbing, and 72 mountain summits in just 31 days. #CNN #News
title: Ultrarunner climbs 72 of the highest US peaks in one month

author: CNN
description: A massive explosion rocked Afghanistan’s capital of Kabul last week igniting one of the bloodiest border conflicts between Afghanistan and neighboring Pakistan in decades. CNN's Sophia Saifi reports. #cnn #afghanistan #pakistan
title: Why are Afghanistan and Pakistan clashing on border?

author: CNN
description: A judge in Illinois said she has “serious concerns” over whether federal law enforcement agents are following her order to avoid violent encounters with protesters and journalists in Chicago. CNN’s Whitney Wild reports.  #CNN #News

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump has called Portland “a war zone” and threatened to send in National Guard troops to restore order. In response, more and more protesters are showing up in inflatable animal costumes to protest federal immigration enforcement operations in the city. CNN spoke to some of the protesters to hear why they are wearing the costumes. #cnn #news
title: The story behind Portland’s inflatable protesters

author: CNN
description: Drones have been spotted over key civilian and military sites in Europe in recent weeks, disrupting airports and sowing chaos. While many European leaders are pointing the finger at Russia, hard evidence that the Kremlin is behind this activity is scarce. CNN’s Katie Polglase investigates. #CNN #News
title: Russian-linked ships spotted in Europe where drone activity has been flagged

author: CNN
description: Hamas’ military wing said “significant efforts and special equipment” are needed to recover the bodies of the remaining Israeli hostages in Gaza. Under the ceasefire agreement, Hamas was supposed to return all of the living and deceased hostages within the first 72 hours. But the group has handed over only nine dead hostages. CNN’s Jeremy Diamond reports.  #CNN #News
title: Anger in Israel as Hamas says it has handed over all bodies it has access to

description: London is hosting a top-tier sumo wrestling tournament for only the second time ever — a five-day event showcasing some of the sport's biggest stars. CNN’s Hanako Montgomery reports. #CNN #news

author: CNN
description: A judge has ordered the Trump administration to immediately halt its efforts to lay off roughly 4,000 federal workers during the government shutdown, calling the move unlawful. The ruling, issued Wednesday, follows a warning from the Office of Management and Budget director that layoffs could climb “north of 10,000.”  #CNN #News
title: Federal judge halts mass federal layoffs amid shutdown

author: CNN
description:
The WNBA just wrapped its most-watched season in history, with soaring team valuations and unprecedented public interest. Audie turns to CNN contributor and host of Naked Sports, @ItsCariChampion, to talk about what the next era of the WNBA could look like: the economics of the game and how a new competitor could redefine ownership, competition, and opportunity for female athletes.

Listen to the full episode of CNN's The Assignment podcast: http://swap.fm/l/twacyt10165

#cnn #news #sports #wnba #caitlinclark #angelreese #basketball #women
title: Why everyone started paying attention to the WNBA | The Assignment

author: CNN
description:
Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez criticized negotiations to end the government shutdown, saying that Republicans “need to pick up a phone.”

“They need to pick up a phone, Katilan. They need to pick up a phone,” Ocasio-Cortez said in a CNN Town Hall on Wednesday, dismissing Speaker Mike Johnson’s argument that Democrats must accept a clean continuing resolution passed by House Republicans last month. #CNN #News
title: 'They need to pick up the phone': AOC, Sanders on efforts to end the Congress stalemate

description: President Donald Trump said today he authorized the CIA to operate inside Venezuela to clamp down on illegal flows of migrants and drugs from the South American nation, but stopped short of saying they would have authority to remove President Nicolas Maduro.

author: CNN
description: Comedian and actor Cheech Marin — one half of the iconic duo Cheech & Chong — has spent decades championing Chicano art and Latino culture. CNN correspondent Julia Vargas Jones sits down with Marin at The Cheech Marin Center for Chicano Art & Culture in Riverside, California, to talk about representation in American museums, the power of art to tell untold stories, and what it means to be Chicano in today’s America. It was recorded as part of Hispanic Heritage Month. #CNN #News
title: Cheech Marin’s mission to elevate Chicano art

author: CNN
description: Vice President JD Vance dismissed racist and antisemitic messages in Young Republicans’ group chats following a POLITICO report revealing the chats were filled with bigoted content from party leaders and a former Trump staffer.   #CNN #News
